header.gameNote: BASKETBALL TRAVELERS CLASSIC AT EUGENE OR

article.headline: Cal State Northridge 90, Portland State 65
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Terrell Jones scored 22 points and Cal State Northridge jumped out to an early 6-0 lead and never trailed, defeating the Portland State Vikings 90-65 on Friday night in the Basketball Travelers Classic. The Matadors 10-0 run to start the second half gave them 16 unanswered points to lead 54-25 with 16:31 to play. They led by as many as 35. Junior Jonathan Heard chipped in 18 points and five rebounds for Cal State Northridge in the season opener. The Matadors out-rebounded Portland State 40-28 and had 21 assists compared to seven by the Vikings. The Vikings were led by Deonte Huff, who scored 13 points. Portland State shot just 15-46 from the field. Cal State Northridge set a McArthur Court record for fouls in one game with 41. The previous record was 40 by Oregon State, March 1, 1947. The two teams combined to tie a McArthur Court record with 68 fouls. The previous mark was set in a game featuring Oregon and Washington on February 28, 1975.
